PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782857894
OL,3,CGermany crash out on penalties to
OL,4,CParaguay in historic World Cup upset
OL,6,FParaguay President Santiago Pena
OL,7,Fdeclared Tuesday as a national holiday
OL,8,Ffor the country following the historic
OL,9,Fwin.
OL,11,FIt came after Paraguay had twice blown
OL,12,Fmatch point to allow Germany back, but
OL,13,FJulian Nagelsmann's side had dominated
OL,14,Fthe game sufficiently to have finished
OL,15,Fthe tie long before that point.
OL,17,FJulio Enciso headed the opening goal
OL,18,Fagainst the run of play in the first
OL,19,Fhalf only for Kai Havertz to hit back
OL,20,Fshortly after half-time to level.
OL,26,@nD@_Tw
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
